  "prompt": "How can we define UPSC?",
  "response": "UPSC stands for Union Public Service Commission. It is a central agency in India responsible for conducting various examinations to recruit candidates for civil services and other government positions. The UPSC is tasked with ensuring that the recruitment process is fair, transparent, and based on merit. Some of the key examinations conducted by the UPSC include the Civil Services Examination (CSE), Indian Forest Service (IFS) Examination, Engineering Services Examination (ESE), and Combined Defence Services (CDS) Examination, among others. The UPSC plays a crucial role in selecting candidates for important administrative roles in the Indian government.",
